g stays at recall/precision 1.0.\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:decisions -->\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: <!-- ANCHOR:verification -->\n74: ## Verification\n75: | Gate | Result |\n76: |---|---|\n77: | sk-code-router-sync + surface-slice-sync + code-surface-path-parse | 21/21 |\n78: | Dangling old-path grep (authored) | Clean |\n79: | Full skill-benchmark suite | 11 failures == clean-HEAD baseline → 0 regressions |\n80: | `validate.sh --strict` (this child) | 0 errors |\n81: <!-- /ANCHOR:verification -->\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: <!-- ANCHOR:limitations -->\n86: ## Known Limitations\n87: - Generated benchmark reports still show old paths; refresh on the next paid live Mode-B run (deferred to 012).\n88: - smart_routing.md prose brace-rows (`{style_guide,…}.md`) left as folder-shorthand (not gated, human-facing only).\n89: <!-- /ANCHOR:limitations -->\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## Post-Completion Follow-Up\n94: Proceed to phase 009 (code-webflow implementation references, 11 files → ~34 parts).\n\n(End of file - total 94 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Implementation Summary: Phase 8 — Split code-opencode Other-Language & Shared References\"\ndescription: \"Outcome of splitting 9 code-opencode docs (typescript/shell trios, javascript quality_standards, shared code_organization + universal_patterns) into 20 topic-cohesive parts and rewiring the language RESOURCE_MAPs, shared tier, parent union, TS_TRIO, and playbook expected_resources; 21/21 router guards green, 0 regressions vs baseline.\"\ncontextType: \"implementation\"\n_memory:\n  continuity:\n    packet_pointer: \"sk-code/018-rust-standards-for-code-opencode/008-code-opencode-other-references\"\n    last_updated_at: \"2026-07-11T14:40:00Z\"\n    last_updated_by: \"claude-code\"\n    recent_action: \"Split applied, router + shared tier rewired, 21/21 guards green, 0 regressions\"\n    next_safe_action: \"Commit phase 008, then proceed to phase 009 (code-webflow implementation references)\"\n    blockers: [