{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783806827322,"sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","part":{"id":"prt_f532c1b37001fKaAvyU1apansN","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","messageID":"msg_f532bda63001mH5NGE79SwVby9","sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":202490,"input":22117,"output":432,"reasoning":229,"cache":{"write":0,"read":179712}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783806830343,"sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","part":{"id":"prt_f532c2705001PVG75525j2IxCE","messageID":"msg_f532c1d8c0017FDCrRGw65sTbl","sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","snapshot":"fe03b20dde9c4dbba7dc0e6f79ecce2c3c838fcc","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783806844167,"sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_VdvDRKkfdduzUEhhgOoOT9Ia","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/README.md","offset":35,"limit":85},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n35: Implementation can produce code that is behaviorally close but still not shippable: a forbidden comment label, a missing authoring checklist, stale generated output, a style violation, or a P0 quality defect that verification would not explain well. The quality mode closes that gap before final evidence is collected.\n36: \n37: ### What It Does\n38: \n39: `code-quality` consumes the parent `sk-code` surface detection, loads the required quality checklist, selects an OpenCode authoring checklist by target path when needed, runs the comment-hygiene checker per modified file, and applies P0/P1/P2 author checks. It can edit existing scoped files to fix gate failures. It does not create new files, dispatch tasks, or produce formal review reports.\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ## 3. QUICK START\n44: \n45: **Step 1: Route after implementation.** Use this mode after the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`) has changed files and before the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`) collects final evidence.\n46: \n47: **Step 2: Load the right checklist.** The mode always loads [`assets/code_quality_checklist.md`](./assets/code_quality_checklist.md). For `.opencode/` targets, it also loads the matching checklist under [`assets/checklists/`](../code-opencode/assets/checklists/).\n48: \n49: **Step 3: Run comment hygiene per modified file.** Use [`scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh`](./scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh) for every modified file that can contain comments.\n50: \n51: **Step 4: Fix or hand back.** Fix in-place quality failures with `Edit`. Hand broader implementation to the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`), root-cause failures to the surface's debugging workflow (`workflow_debug.md`), and final evidence to the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`).\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ## 4. HOW IT WORKS\n56: \n57: The mode sits between implementation and verification. It reads the changed files, resolves surface identity from shared router references, applies the right checklist family, runs comment hygiene, and checks P0/P1/P2 status. P0 blocks completion. P1 is fixed unless the user accepts a documented risk. P2 is fixed when cheap or explicitly deferred with a reason.\n58: \n59: ### Target-Path Routing\n60: \n61: OpenCode authoring targets route to specific checklists: skills, agents, commands, spec folders, MCP servers, language files, and config each have their own checklist. Webflow/frontend work uses the code quality checklist and shared universal standards.\n62: \n63: ### Mutation Boundary\n64: \n65: This mode can edit already-scoped files because author-side quality correction is part of implementation. It cannot write new files and cannot dispatch subagents. Findings-only review belongs to `code-review`.\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 5. INTEGRATION & NAVIGATION\n70: \n71: ### When To Use This Mode\n72: \n73: Use it when a change is already written and needs standards enforcement before final verification: skill authoring, script changes, config changes, frontend quality, comment hygiene, or stale generated-output checks. Skip it when the task is to build new behavior, debug a failing symptom, verify non-mutating evidence, or review without editing.\n74: \n75: ### Related Skills\n76: \n77: | Skill | Relationship |\n78: |---|---|\n79: | `sk-code` | Parent hub that routes the quality workflow here |\n80: | `code-webflow` / `code-opencode` | Surface skills that implement/change files, own root-cause debugging, and gather verification evidence via the implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine. |\n81: | `code-review` | Produces findings-first reports when no author-side editing is wanted |\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## 6. VERIFICATION\n86: \n87: | Check | How to run it |\n88: |---|---|\n89: | Comment hygiene | `bash .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh <modified-file>` |\n90: | Distribution drift | `bash .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh` when generated artifacts are involved |\n91: | Skill structure | Validate changed skill docs with the project documentation validator when applicable |\n92: | Final claim | Hand to the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`); this mode does not make done or works claims |\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## 7. RELATED DOCUMENTS\n97: \n98: | Document | Purpose |\n99: |---|---|\n100: | [`SKILL.md`](./SKILL.md) | Runtime contract for the quality mode |\n101: | [`assets/code_quality_checklist.md`](./assets/code_quality_checklist.md) | Required quality checklist before implementation completion claims |\n102: | [`assets/checklists/`](../code-opencode/assets/checklists/) | Target-path OpenCode authoring checklists |\n103: | [`scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh`](./scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh) | Per-file comment-hygiene checker |\n104: | [`scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh`](./scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh) | Generated artifact drift checker |\n105: | [`../shared/references/stack_detection.md`](../shared/references/stack_detection.md) | Shared surface detection |\n106: | [`../shared/references/phase_detection.md`](../shared/references/phase_detection.md) | Lifecycle placement for the quality gate |\n107: | [`../shared/references/universal/code_quality_standards.md`](../shared/references/universal/code_quality_standards.md) | Universal quality standards |\n\n(End of file - total 107 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Implementation can produce code that is behaviorally close but still not shippable: a forbidden comment label, a missing authoring checklist, stale generated output, a style violation, or a P0 quality defect that verification would not explain well. The quality mode closes that gap before final evidence is collected.\n\n### What It Does\n\n`code-quality` consumes the parent `sk-code` surface detection, loads the required quality checklist, selects an OpenCode authoring checklist by target path when needed, runs the comment-hygiene checker per modified file, and applies P0/P1/P2 author checks. It can edit existing scoped files to fix gate failures. It does not create new files, dispatch tasks, or produce formal review reports.\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK START\n\n**Step 1: Route after implementation.** Use this mode after the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`) has changed files and before the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`) collects final evidence.\n\n**Step 2: Load the right checklist.** The mode always loads [`assets/code_quality_checklist.md`](./assets/code_quality_checklist.md). For `.opencode/` targets, it also loads the matching checklist under [`assets/checklists/`](../code-opencode/assets/checklists/).\n\n**Step 3: Run comment hygiene per modified file.** Use [`scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh`](./scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh) for every modified file that can contain comments.\n\n**Step 4: Fix or hand back.** Fix in-place quality failures with `Edit`. Hand broader implementation to the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`), root-cause failures to the surface's debugging workflow (`workflow_debug.md`), and final evidence to the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`).\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/README.md","text":"Implementation can produce code that is behaviorally close but still not shippable: a forbidden comment label, a missing authoring checklist, stale generated output, a style violation, or a P0 quality defect that verification would not explain well. The quality mode closes that gap before final evidence is collected.\n\n### What It Does\n\n`code-quality` consumes the parent `sk-code` surface detection, loads the required quality checklist, selects an OpenCode authoring checklist by target path when needed, runs the comment-hygiene checker per modified file, and applies P0/P1/P2 author checks. It can edit existing scoped files to fix gate failures. It does not create new files, dispatch tasks, or produce formal review reports.\n\n---\n\n## 3. QUICK START\n\n**Step 1: Route after implementation.** Use this mode after the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`) has changed files and before the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`) collects final evidence.\n\n**Step 2: Load the right checklist.** The mode always loads [`assets/code_quality_checklist.md`](./assets/code_quality_checklist.md). For `.opencode/` targets, it also loads the matching checklist under [`assets/checklists/`](../code-opencode/assets/checklists/).\n\n**Step 3: Run comment hygiene per modified file.** Use [`scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh`](./scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh) for every modified file that can contain comments.\n\n**Step 4: Fix or hand back.** Fix in-place quality failures with `Edit`. Hand broader implementation to the surface skill (`code-webflow` / `code-opencode`), root-cause failures to the surface's debugging workflow (`workflow_debug.md`), and final evidence to the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. HOW IT WORKS\n\nThe mode sits between implementation and verification. It reads the changed files, resolves surface identity from shared router references, applies the right checklist family, runs comment hygiene, and checks P0/P1/P2 status. P0 blocks completion. P1 is fixed unless the user accepts a documented risk. P2 is fixed when cheap or explicitly deferred with a reason.\n\n### Target-Path Routing\n\nOpenCode authoring targets route to specific checklists: skills, agents, commands, spec folders, MCP servers, language files, and config each have their own checklist. Webflow/frontend work uses the code quality checklist and shared universal standards.\n\n### Mutation Boundary\n\nThis mode can edit already-scoped files because author-side quality correction is part of implementation. It cannot write new files and cannot dispatch subagents. Findings-only review belongs to `code-review`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. INTEGRATION & NAVIGATION\n\n### When To Use This Mode\n\nUse it when a change is already written and needs standards enforcement before final verification: skill authoring, script changes, config changes, frontend quality, comment hygiene, or stale generated-output checks. Skip it when the task is to build new behavior, debug a failing symptom, verify non-mutating evidence, or review without editing.\n\n### Related Skills\n\n| Skill | Relationship |\n|---|---|\n| `sk-code` | Parent hub that routes the quality workflow here |\n| `code-webflow` / `code-opencode` | Surface skills that implement/change files, own root-cause debugging, and gather verification evidence via the implement → debug → verify workflow doctrine. |\n| `code-review` | Produces findings-first reports when no author-side editing is wanted |\n\n---\n\n## 6. VERIFICATION\n\n| Check | How to run it |\n|---|---|\n| Comment hygiene | `bash .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh <modified-file>` |\n| Distribution drift | `bash .opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh` when generated artifacts are involved |\n| Skill structure | Validate changed skill docs with the project documentation validator when applicable |\n| Final claim | Hand to the surface's verification workflow (`workflow_verify.md`); this mode does not make done or works claims |\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED DOCUMENTS\n\n| Document | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| [`SKILL.md`](./SKILL.md) | Runtime contract for the quality mode |\n| [`assets/code_quality_checklist.md`](./assets/code_quality_checklist.md) | Required quality checklist before implementation completion claims |\n| [`assets/checklists/`](../code-opencode/assets/checklists/) | Target-path OpenCode authoring checklists |\n| [`scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh`](./scripts/check-comment-hygiene.sh) | Per-file comment-hygiene checker |\n| [`scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh`](./scripts/check-dist-staleness.sh) | Generated artifact drift checker |\n| [`../shared/references/stack_detection.md`](../shared/references/stack_detection.md) | Shared surface detection |\n| [`../shared/references/phase_detection.md`](../shared/references/phase_detection.md) | Lifecycle placement for the quality gate |\n| [`../shared/references/universal/code_quality_standards.md`](../shared/references/universal/code_quality_standards.md) | Universal quality standards |","lineStart":35,"lineEnd":107,"totalLines":107,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/README.md","time":{"start":1783806844163,"end":1783806844166}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0eb0e43759bbe2d4016a52bb7c0e848191a3b8abd04f624ac5"}},"id":"prt_f532c5cc8001jrt0mknqFaJynN","sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","messageID":"msg_f532c1d8c0017FDCrRGw65sTbl"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783806844218,"sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_k5VWY3gCcnLMh2t102SL1JaE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/manual_testing_playbook/quality-gate/quality-checklist.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/manual_testing_playbook/quality-gate/quality-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: CQ-001\n3: category: quality-gate\n4: title: 'Quality gate routes to the code-quality checklist'\n5: expected_intent: QUALITY\n6: expected_resources:\n7:   - assets/code_quality_checklist.md\n8: version: 1.0.0.0\n9: ---\n10: \n11: # CQ-001: Quality Gate Routes to the Checklist\n12: \n13: ## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n14: \n15: - Prompt: `run the comment hygiene quality gate and check p0 p1 p2 standards before marking this done`\n16: - Expected intent: `QUALITY`\n17: \n18: The `QUALITY` intent must resolve to code-quality's single routable checklist. This is a thin, deliberately narrow Type-1 route; the skill's real routing precision is target-path-keyed and covered by a unit test, and its parent discoverability is the hub `quality` signal.\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: CQ-001\ncategory: quality-gate\ntitle: 'Quality gate routes to the code-quality checklist'\nexpected_intent: QUALITY\nexpected_resources:\n  - assets/code_quality_checklist.md\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# CQ-001: Quality Gate Routes to the Checklist\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Prompt: `run the comment hygiene quality gate and check p0 p1 p2 standards before marking this done`\n- Expected intent: `QUALITY`\n\nThe `QUALITY` intent must resolve to code-quality's single routable checklist. This is a thin, deliberately narrow Type-1 route; the skill's real routing precision is target-path-keyed and covered by a unit test, and its parent discoverability is the hub `quality` signal.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/manual_testing_playbook/quality-gate/quality-checklist.md","text":"---\nid: CQ-001\ncategory: quality-gate\ntitle: 'Quality gate routes to the code-quality checklist'\nexpected_intent: QUALITY\nexpected_resources:\n  - assets/code_quality_checklist.md\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# CQ-001: Quality Gate Routes to the Checklist\n\n## 2. SCENARIO CONTRACT\n\n- Prompt: `run the comment hygiene quality gate and check p0 p1 p2 standards before marking this done`\n- Expected intent: `QUALITY`\n\nThe `QUALITY` intent must resolve to code-quality's single routable checklist. This is a thin, deliberately narrow Type-1 route; the skill's real routing precision is target-path-keyed and covered by a unit test, and its parent discoverability is the hub `quality` signal.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":18,"totalLines":18,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/manual_testing_playbook/quality-gate/quality-checklist.md","time":{"start":1783806844210,"end":1783806844217}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0eb0e43759bbe2d4016a52bb7c0e988191a825de6cf0f697f3"}},"id":"prt_f532c5d250013Xb3golqKYVnB9","sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","messageID":"msg_f532c1d8c0017FDCrRGw65sTbl"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783806844241,"sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3DP5qKagDGntx1by29KEjhad","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/debugging/error_recovery.md","offset":95,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/debugging/error_recovery.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ## 5. GENERAL RECOVERY PROTOCOL\n99: \n100: When any failure occurs:\n101: \n102: 1. **Document** the failure (error message, context)\n103: 2. **Isolate** the problem (single file, single change)\n104: 3. **Verify** prerequisites (tools installed, credentials valid)\n105: 4. **Retry** with verbose output\n106: 5. **Escalate** if 3+ attempts fail (see SKILL.md escalation rules)\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n111: \n112: - [cdn_deployment.md](../deployment/cdn_deployment.md) - CDN deployment workflow\n113: - [minification_guide.md](../deployment/minification_guide.md) - Minification procedures\n114: - [debugging_workflows.md](./debugging_workflows.md) - General debugging\n\n(End of file - total 114 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n---\n\n## 5. GENERAL RECOVERY PROTOCOL\n\nWhen any failure occurs:\n\n1. **Document** the failure (error message, context)\n2. **Isolate** the problem (single file, single change)\n3. **Verify** prerequisites (tools installed, credentials valid)\n4. **Retry** with verbose output\n5. **Escalate** if 3+ attempts fail (see SKILL.md escalation rules)\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [cdn_deployment.md](../deployment/cdn_deployment.md) - CDN deployment workflow\n- [minification_guide.md](../deployment/minification_guide.md) - Minification procedures\n- [debugging_workflows.md](./debugging_workflows.md) - General debugging","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/debugging/error_recovery.md","text":"\n---\n\n## 5. GENERAL RECOVERY PROTOCOL\n\nWhen any failure occurs:\n\n1. **Document** the failure (error message, context)\n2. **Isolate** the problem (single file, single change)\n3. **Verify** prerequisites (tools installed, credentials valid)\n4. **Retry** with verbose output\n5. **Escalate** if 3+ attempts fail (see SKILL.md escalation rules)\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [cdn_deployment.md](../deployment/cdn_deployment.md) - CDN deployment workflow\n- [minification_guide.md](../deployment/minification_guide.md) - Minification procedures\n- [debugging_workflows.md](./debugging_workflows.md) - General debugging","lineStart":95,"lineEnd":114,"totalLines":114,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/debugging/error_recovery.md","time":{"start":1783806844234,"end":1783806844240}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0eb0e43759bbe2d4016a52bb7c0ea08191831d6e2bf0418781"}},"id":"prt_f532c5d33001F4KRPkGkrUpCjG","sessionID":"ses_0acd715bbffezygsvb9LhK73F1","messageID":"msg_f532c1d8c0017FDCrRGw65sTbl"}}
