c/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/008-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/013-skill-benchmark-fidelity-track/tasks.md:\n  Line 66: - [x] T-301 Full deep-improvement vitest suite green (295/295, 24 files; +5 new) + `sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` 4/4. Router benchmark unchanged (agg 46, D2 47, D3 32); advisory signals additive.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/008-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/013-skill-benchmark-fidelity-track/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 89: | Drift guard | `npx vitest run skill-benchmark/tests/sk-code-router-sync.vitest.ts` | PASS — 4/4 green |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-3/logs/fanout-lineage.out:\n  Line 167: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487041245,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfeb66ceffe83jWKFM65pCjvi\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_GMdyRQhqjviir3EBKxIjCt3d\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code\",\"include\":\"*.{md,json,ts,js,cjs}\"},\"output\":\"Found 8 matches\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/manual_testing_playbook/09--tooling-and-hooks/comment-hygiene-hook.md:\\n  Line 130: **Where `deep-review` consumes it.** `deep-review` audits four dimensions — correctness, security, **traceability**, and maintainability (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:80`). The comment-hygiene envelope feeds the **traceability** dimension: a comment that still points at a spec path, packet/phase number, or ADR/REQ/task/finding id is exactly the kind of unstable, rot-prone reference the traceability pass is meant to catch, and the author-side envelope tells the reviewer which such references were already flagged, fixed, or deferred. `deep-review` then classifies each surviving finding by blocking severity — P0/P1/P2 (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:84`) — and those severity gates roll up into the release-readiness verdict, PASS / CONDITIONAL / FAIL (`.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/README.md:27`). A comment-hygiene deferral the author labelled low-risk typically lands as a P2 advisory that rides a PASS; one that obscures a real traceability defect can be escalated by the reviewer through its own adversarial re-read.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/quick_reference.md:\\n  Line 61: - [review_mode_contract.yaml](../../../deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml) - Canonical review-mode contract manifest (s...\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/z_archive/008-deep-improvement-skill-benchmark-mode/015-post-remediation-deep-review/review-mimo-v25pro-run2/raw-logs/iter-005.stdout.log:\n  Line 3: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1780410429576,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1774511b4ffeVeqthFMdzHuAOg\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_ae0de3fd212e4fd9804fd1e3\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/skills/deep-improvement/**/*\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/SKILL.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/assets/model-benchmark/benchmark-fixtures/README.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-improvement/scripts/skill-benchmark/d4-ablation.cjs\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/s